\cf0 \strokec2 This matters for a few reasons:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 It lowers the upload barrier.
\f0\b0  Someone who only shot crowd footage or a bar scene outside the stadium felt like their content "didn't qualify." Now it does. You get more uploads per event.\

\f2\b It makes the virtual attendance experience richer.
\f0\b0  A teenager in London doesn't just want to see the setlist \'97 she wants to 
\f4\i feel
\f0\i0  what it was like to be there. The chaos of the pit, the vibe of the VIP deck, the crowd losing it. That's atmosphere, not just performance.\

\f2\b It creates a second browse axis.
\f0\b0  Right now you'd filter by song. With location/vibe categories, you'd filter by 
\f4\i experience type
\f0\i0  \'97 "show me all the pit footage" or "what was the venue like?"\

\f2\b Implementation-wise
\f0\b0  it fits cleanly into what you already have \'97 just expanding the tag taxonomy beyond songs to include 
\f2\b location/vibe tags
\f0\b0  as a parallel category on the media row. Could be as simple as a second optional tag type: 
\f5\fs26 tag_type: 'song' | 'location' | 'vibe'
\f0\fs24 .\
