\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 Why Concerts First Is Correct\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 A few things make concerts the ideal beachhead:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Demand signal is already proven.
\f0\b0  Fan-shot concert clips on YouTube get 10M+ views organically. People are already doing this behavior \'97 just unorganized across TikTok/Instagram/YouTube.\

\f2\b The pain is acute and emotional.
\f0\b0  Being priced out of a show you wanted to attend is a specific, felt frustration. The Morgan Wallen teenager in London is a real person with a real problem. That emotional hook drives word of mouth.\

\f2\b Upload motivation is high.
\f0\b0  Concert attendees are 
\f4\i proud
\f0\i0  of their footage. They want to share it. The social currency of "I was there" is strong.\

\f2\b Defined entity structure.
\f0\b0  Artist 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Tour 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Show is clean. You know exactly what the taxonomy looks like before you build.\

\f2\b Community already exists.
\f0\b0  Fan communities around artists are passionate, organized, and vocal. One Reddit post in r/MorganWallen or r/Beyonce could drive hundreds of uploads.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

