\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 How You Actually Get There\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The path isn't cold outreach to artists. It's:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Step 1 \'97 Build the artist's page without asking permission.
\f0\b0  Morgan Wallen's Showside page exists whether Morgan Wallen knows about it or not. It looks incredible because fans already uploaded. That page 
\f4\i is
\f0\i0  the pitch.\

\f2\b Step 2 \'97 The content does the outreach.
\f0\b0  Artist's social team finds a clip of a surprise moment from last Tuesday's show. It's on Showside. They repost it. That's level 2 happening organically.\

\f2\b Step 3 \'97 You reach the team not the artist.
\f0\b0  You never cold email Morgan Wallen. You find his tour manager or social media manager \'97 real humans with real jobs who are actively looking for fan content \'97 and you show them the page. The pitch is 
\f4\i "your fans are already here, we just organized it."
\f0\i0 \

\f2\b Step 4 \'97 You offer them something.
\f0\b0  Not money. Access. An artist dashboard where they can see all fan uploads from their shows, download clips, see what songs got filmed most. That's genuinely useful to a social media team. Now Showside has a reason to be in their workflow permanently.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

