\f2\b \cf0 3. Ticketing Affiliate
\f0\b0  Someone watches 30 minutes of Beyonc\'e9 footage on Showside and then sees 
\f4\i "She's playing Miami in March \'97 tickets from $180"
\f0\i0  with an affiliate link to Ticketmaster/StubHub. That person is the highest-intent concert buyer on the internet right now. Affiliate commissions on ticket sales are meaningful. This is 
\f2\b easy to implement early
\f0\b0  and requires no advertiser relationships.\

\f2\b 4. Promoted Placement
\f0\b0  Artists or promoters pay to have their entity page featured, or to have their upcoming show surfaced to users browsing similar artists. Not traditional ads \'97 more like 
\f2\b native promotion
\f0\b0  that fits the experience. 
\f4\i "Fans of this artist also uploaded footage from..."
\f0\i0  could be organic or paid.\

