\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The architectural decisions that matter most at scale are already made correctly in your codebase:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Direct uploads
\f0\b0  \'97 files go from user's device straight to Mux/R2, never through your server. This is the right call. If uploads went through Vercel, a spike in uploads would overwhelm your serverless functions. They don't \'97 so it doesn't matter.\

\f2\b Database triggers for counters
\f0\b0  \'97 all your like counts, view counts, upload counts are maintained by DB triggers not application code. This prevents race conditions under high concurrency.\

\f2\b RLS policies
\f0\b0  \'97 Supabase Row Level Security means the database enforces access rules, not your app code. Scales cleanly.\

\f2\b CDN delivery
\f0\b0  \'97 photos are on Cloudflare's CDN, videos on Mux's CDN. Content is served from the edge, not a single origin server.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
